## Key Insights

### Cost Efficiency
CNG and EV demonstrated the lowest operational costs while Petrol and E85 remained competitive.

### Environmental Impact
EV and E85 showed lower emissions compared to conventional fuels.

### Vehicle Age Analysis
Operating costs generally increased as vehicle age increased, highlighting the importance of maintenance planning.

### E85 Evaluation
E85 provided noticeable pump-price savings but experienced reduced mileage efficiency, creating a trade-off between fuel price and real-world running cost.

